OL,3,CERS-2 satellite returns to Earth's
OL,4,Catmosphere after almost 30 years
OL,6,FThe satellite was launched in 1995
OL,7,Ffollowing on from its sister
OL,8,Fsatellite, ERS-1, which had launched
OL,9,Ffour years earlier.
OL,11,FAt the time, they were both the most
OL,12,Fsophisticated Earth observation
OL,13,Fsatellites ever developed.
OL,15,FIn 2011, Esa retired the still-
OL,16,Ffunctioning ERS-2 and began the
OL,17,Fprocess of deorbiting.
